Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended) plus a matching XAML page with compiled bindings:

**ViewModel:**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        IsBusy = true;
        try
        {
            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);
            Name = "Widget Pro";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable`, `IsBusy`) with `PropertyChanged` notifications, and a `LoadCommand` from the `[RelayCommand]` attribute.

**XAML page with compiled bindings:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage">

    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" IsVisible="{Binding IsBusy}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **`x:DataType`** at the page root enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe)
- **`[ObservableProperty]`** generates the property + `PropertyChanged` raise automatically
- **`[RelayCommand]`** generates `LoadCommand` and disables the button while `LoadAsync` is running
- If using DI, inject the VM via constructor instead of declaring it in XAML — see the `maui-dependency-injection` skill

Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time.
